data.description: Come check out this one story brick home on 2.19 acres in a beautiful established neighborhood. The hard work has been done for you! These owners have only been here for a few months and they removed all of the old carpet with plans to replace with vinyl flooring. Sadly, life happens and they are forced to sell before being able to complete the work. There are 5 outbuildings on this land! A garage, a chapel, a barn and 2 additional buildings that could be used as mini houses, pool house, etc. There are 2 gazebos and even a mini-golf course! And wait for it - an inground pool too! Beautiful lawn with flowering plants and trees. There is a decorative bridge over a concrete pond. The front yard is fenced, the back yard is wooded, concrete driveway. With a little time and effort this place could be a showstopper! 3 bedrooms, 2 full baths, full unfinished basement with framed partitions. Brand new aluminum handicapped ramp to front door, wooden ramp to side door. Agent related to seller.
